                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Editorial Note</hi>
                </head>
                <p>No official record of the substance of this conversation has been found. The
                    information set forth above is derived from the Log, <hi rend="italic"
                    >ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_530">p. 530</ref>. According to Elliott Roosevelt
                    (p. 107), Churchill arrived with news that de Gaulle had agreed to come to
                    Casablanca. For the text of de Gaulle’s message of January 20, 1943, to
                    Churchill, accepting the invitation to attend the Casablanca Conference, see de
                    Gaulle, <hi rend="italic">Documents</hi>, p. 128. De Gaulle arrived at
                    Casablanca on January 22.</p>
            </div>
